{"_id":"3PtJOwfNoEVDETzK","name":"Kayte","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Human (Lhazaar origin) bookstore/arcana curio shop (and tea importer!) proprietor in Regalport. Daughter of an infirm mage of some repute, she now runs the shop. She is Rus’s hookup for all arcane goods, from tomes of arcane knowledge to wands/spell reagents.</p>\n</div>","img":"modules/monks-enhanced-journal/assets/person.png","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"person","relationships":[{"type":"place","id":"PX2jYO7Tf4JVWQr9","relationship":"Place of Residence","hidden":false},{"type":"shop","id":"Jej0o1tZOJtaxrP2","relationship":"Proprietor of Shop","hidden":false}],"scrollPos":"{\".tab.details .tab-inner\":0,\".tab.description .tab-inner\":0,\".relationships .items-list\":0}","role":"","location":"Regalport","race":"Human","gender":"Female","age":"","pronoun":"Her/She","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"Arcane Merchant","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","_lasttab":"description","fields":{"race":{"value":true},"gender":{"value":true},"age":{"value":true},"eyes":{"value":true},"skin":{"value":false},"hair":{"value":true},"pronoun":{"value":true},"profession":{"value":true},"voice":{"value":true},"faction":{"value":false},"height":{"value":false},"weight":{"value":false},"traits":{"value":true},"ideals":{"value":false},"bonds":{"value":false},"flaws":{"value":true},"longterm":{"value":false},"shortterm":{"value":false},"beliefs":{"value":true},"secret":{"value":true}}},"_document-sheet-registrar":{"type":"person"},"journal-backlinks":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_q8ht2jxoek","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar Lore#/CF_SEP/Lhazaar Principalities#/CF_SEP/02.09.12. People","color":"#800000"}}}
{"_id":"3hooq1e9mFdU5dNB","name":"Officer's Hall and Armory","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Officer's Mess and Armory</h1>\n<p>This tiny chamber is crammed with chests and neatly ordered weapon racks. The armory is secured with a good lock (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} check (–2)) and trapped with a harpoon trap at each door.</p>\n<p>Among all the crates and weapons racks there are a couple tables here. The officers gather here in the evening to have thier  meal seperate from the crew.</p>\n<p>The weapon racks hold 20 clubs, 12 heavy crossbows, 20 cutlasses , 50 javelins, 12 shortspears, and 20 grappling hooks each attached to 50 feet of rope.</p>\n<p>Two chests contain 500 heavy crossbow bolts each, while three other chests each hold 12 flasks of alchemist’s fire. Four other chests each contain a breastplate, chain shirt, and buckler.</p>\n<p>The ship’s master gunner, @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Riaris Krine]{Riaris Krine}, is meticulous in her job and quickly spots any obvious thefts, in which case an immediate search of the crew’s lockers is made. Anyone found in possession of stolen items from the armory is given six lashes with the cat for a first offense, or is keelhauled for a second offense.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Krornik Kragshard]{Krornik Kragshard} and @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Cut-Throat Grok]{Cut-Throat Grok} sleep here in the evenings.</p>\n<h2 class=\"trap\">Harpoon Trap</h2>\n<p><strong>Type:</strong> Mechanical; <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} Check:</strong> Yes, at –1; <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} Check:</strong> Yes, at –1</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger:</strong> If the door handle is not used in a specific way when the door is opened a harpoon will shoot at the door.</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> The pirate that triggers the trap must make an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} roll to dive clear or be struck by the harpoon ([[/r d8x+d6x=]] damage).</p>\n<p> </p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L91WkUzg75E8tVjM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dljw0qnmnui","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Locations on the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"3wMLwdSJktboBKC3","name":"No Honor among Thieves","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">No Honor among Thieves</h1>\n<p>This event occurs as the mourner's come upon an attack by another pirate ship already underway. The mourner's first sight the battle from a mile away and come upon it just as the pirates have disabled the merchant ship and now prepare to board her. </p>\n<aside class=\"read-aloud\">\n<p>A Brelish galleon lurches from the impact of a catapult shot upon its stern that shatters its rudder. It heels over hard and feathers until its sails luff and it drifts to a stop. Its attacker, a Lhazaar frigate, runs in hard to guard its prize.</p>\n</aside>\n<p>The frigate <em>Howl of Risia</em>, under Captain Gortus Svard, is moving in on the mourners’ ship to prevent it from taking the prize it has been pursuing for the last few hours: the galleon <em>Duchess' Kiss</em> out of Sharn. The <em>Howl of Risia</em> does not attack or pursue the mourners should they avoid confrontation. However, if the mourners linger or attempt to attack the drekar or the disabled galleon, the <em>Howl of Risia</em> turns on the mourners and attempts to sink them.</p>\n<p>The <em>Howl of Risia</em> begins adjacent to the <em>Duchess' Kiss</em>, heading toward the mourners. If the <em>Devil’s Pallor </em>engages the mourners’ ship, the <em>Duchess' Kiss</em> (which starts with a speed of 0,) tries to get underway again and flee the battle in 1d4 rounds.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Frigate]:</span> <em>Howl of Risia</em></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Pirate] (34):</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.First Mate] (1):</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Galleon]:</span> <em>Duchess' Kiss</em></li>\n</ul>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_slwk1t4xhcl","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Savage Tales","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"47d2NQUdzuL5nQkX","name":"Ghost","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>warforged envoy (aka the smaller models made for speed). Quiet, but likes keeping little snacks or sweets on her person to give her fleshy friends when it looks like they could use a pick-me-up. Problem is, she doesn't keep track of when/if things have gone stale, and wouldn't be able to tell anyways. Some of her comrades found it an annoying quirk, Daina found it endearing and would always take the sweets when offered, even if it meant putting it in her pocket and \"saving it for later.\" Ghost was often sent to scout ahead of patrols on her own, taking out enemy soldiers or lookouts along the way whether they spotted her first or not. She didn't like to talk or make a big deal of that, and after a while simply started dragging the bodies off into the brush before returning to the patrol so that they wouldn't ask her or comment about it.</p>\n<p>Last time she saw Ghost was on front, but when she was briefly in New Cyre she met a small contingent of warforged settlers who told her that Ghost was working at a bakery in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Skyway]. Daina found this one hard to believe, because as much as Ghost loved feeding her friends, why the hell would a bakery in the Skyway hire a baker who couldn't taste the food? But stranger things have happened.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-bestiary/humanoids/warforged/warforged-02.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"person","relationships":[],"role":"","location":"","race":"Warforged","gender":"","age":"8","pronoun":"She/Her","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","_lasttab":"description","fields":{"race":{"value":true},"gender":{"value":false},"age":{"value":true},"eyes":{"value":true},"skin":{"value":false},"hair":{"value":true},"pronoun":{"value":true},"profession":{"value":true},"voice":{"value":true},"faction":{"value":false},"height":{"value":false},"weight":{"value":false},"traits":{"value":true},"ideals":{"value":false},"bonds":{"value":false},"flaws":{"value":true},"longterm":{"value":false},"shortterm":{"value":false},"beliefs":{"value":false},"secret":{"value":false}},"scrollPos":"{\".tab.details .tab-inner\":0,\".tab.description .tab-inner\":0,\".relationships .items-list\":0}"},"_document-sheet-registrar":{"type":"person"},"journal-backlinks":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_6nu2k3j5j03","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar Lore#/CF_SEP/Lhazaar Principalities#/CF_SEP/02.09.12. People#/CF_SEP/Potential Crew","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"50t3vOrETGvU1bQL","name":"Mess Hall","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Mess Hall</h1>\n<p>The Mess Hall hasa storage room immediately to the left that holds more equipment for Grok as outlined in the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Quartermasters Store]{Quartermasters Store}.</p>\n<p>The rest of the mess hall contains three tables, number crates and barrels with supplies of food stuff. There are score of chickens and three goats that freely wander this chamber. The goats are meant to be caged but have a distressing tendency to escape their bonds. </p>\n<p>Evening meals are taken here and during the evening there is often gambling or other entertainments to be had here.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L91WkUzg75E8tVjM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dljw0qnmnui","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Locations on the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"5RGVr2PZuxDWasOe","name":"Brunark","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Leader of a small dock working group on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Cliffscrape]. Brunark had the misfortune to cross paths with Trucco while carrying a sack of gold and a nice dagger.</p>\n</div>","img":"modules/monks-enhanced-journal/assets/person.png","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"person","scrollPos":"{\".tab.details .tab-inner\":0,\".tab.description .tab-inner\":0,\".relationships .items-list\":0}","role":"Dock Foreman","location":"Docks of Cliffscrape","race":"Dwarf","gender":"","age":"","pronoun":"He/Him","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"Bald","profession":"Dock Foreman","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","_lasttab":"description","fields":{"race":{"value":true},"gender":{"value":false},"age":{"value":true},"eyes":{"value":true},"skin":{"value":false},"hair":{"value":true},"pronoun":{"value":true},"profession":{"value":true},"voice":{"value":true},"faction":{"value":false},"height":{"value":false},"weight":{"value":false},"traits":{"value":true},"ideals":{"value":false},"bonds":{"value":false},"flaws":{"value":true},"longterm":{"value":true},"shortterm":{"value":true},"beliefs":{"value":true},"secret":{"value":true}},"relationships":[{"type":"place","id":"Z7nxit79IxWFF1NB","relationship":"Place of Residence","hidden":false}]},"_document-sheet-registrar":{"type":"person"},"journal-backlinks":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_q8ht2jxoek","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar Lore#/CF_SEP/Lhazaar Principalities#/CF_SEP/02.09.12. People","color":"#800000"}}}
