{"_id":"74EZcqJ5lT4XnZaH","name":"Wreck of the Carcanus","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Wreck of the Carcanus</h1>\n<p>The Carcanus limped into the Teeth after the kraken’s epic battle with the Sea Hags. The crew did not make it and Tressa has since taken its usable goods, but the magical sails remain intact.</p>\n<p>The Carcanus lies in 60’ of water—just deep enough to require either aquatic characters or magic of some sort. Cutting the sails free takes at least 15 minutes. They can then be hoisted aboard by the crew and put in place in 2d6 hours.</p>\n<p> Sharks (200): 2d6 man-eaters and two great whites are in the area.</p>\n<p> Booty: Loot (the ship has been mostly looted), Sharkskin Sails.</p>\n<p>Sharkskin Sails: Made from the hide of the great ugak Walking God, Jinka-Tahn, these slick gray sails increase the Travel Speed of any vessel mounting them by one.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_slwk1t4xhcl","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Savage Tales","color":"#000000"},"journal-backlinks":{"references":{}}}}
