{"_id":"E8oHB2WzzqVCFQrE","name":"Campaign Summary","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Campaign Summary</h1>\n<h2>Campaign Summary</h2>\n<p>From here you can expect the following to happen over the course of the campaign arc.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>You start the campaign press-ganged onto a Pirate Ship.</li>\n<li>You can expect to find your freedom from Prince Rockface.</li>\n<li>The campaign will be on rails for the first 4-8 sessions while you are a crew member of the <em>Storm Reaver</em>.</li>\n<li>You will have an opportunity to acquire your own ship, through mutiny or other means. </li>\n<li>Once you acquire your own ship, the Lhazaar (and Seas of Eberron) become a large sand box that will be driven by your actions to try and help those that are still alive from Cyre.</li>\n<li>There will be space in the campaign for you to assist Cyrans through piracy and treasure hunting. You can even to attempt to acquire land or a principality for Cyrans. What will you choose?</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Campaign Opening</h2>\n<p>Your journey has taken you to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport} in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Lhazaar Principalities]{Lhazaar Principalities}. You all have come here for different reasons. But each of you find yourselves at an inn called @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.The Salty Dog and The Baron]{the Salty Dog and the Baron}. The night that followed with much drinking, gambling and sea shanties.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Or so you think. You wake in the morning, not remembering much after a certain point. You find yourselves in the hold of a ship out at sea. You are press-ganged, and forced to join the crew of the <em>Storm Reaver</em>, captained by the despicable Mika Rockface. Captain Mika Rockface, infamous as the Prince of the ruthless @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Cloudreaver Principality]{Cloudreaver Principality}. Prince Rockface boldly press gangs you from under the noses of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Seadragon Principality]{Seadragon Principality}.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":10},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_sfbrzx24rkb","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Player Character Guide","color":"#000000"},"journal-backlinks":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"F9EEIAuoIfEMzVD5","name":"Elisie Belkarin","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>Personality:</strong> Elegant, enthusiastic, kind.</p>\n<p><strong>How she met Trucco:</strong> As part of an artistic group (with the name Delirium), taught him at an early age some rope tricks while on Metrol.</p>\n<p><strong>Last interaction/rumor:</strong> Her artistic group went to perform for the upper class of the city. In later years Trucco met with her again in a Hrazhak game, she told him that her group was doing really well, having shows for Prince Oargev ir'Wynarn himself.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/elisie-belkarin.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"person","relationships":[],"fields":{"race":{"value":true},"gender":{"value":true},"age":{"value":true},"eyes":{"value":true},"skin":{"value":false},"hair":{"value":true},"pronoun":{"value":true},"profession":{"value":true},"voice":{"value":true},"faction":{"value":false},"height":{"value":false},"weight":{"value":false},"traits":{"value":true},"ideals":{"value":false},"bonds":{"value":false},"flaws":{"value":true},"longterm":{"value":true},"shortterm":{"value":true},"beliefs":{"value":true},"secret":{"value":true}},"role":"","location":"","race":"Half-elf","gender":"Femaale","age":"","pronoun":"She/they","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"Orange","profession":"Rope-dancer, illusionist, sword fighter","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","_lasttab":"description","scrollPos":"{\".tab.details .tab-inner\":0,\".tab.description .tab-inner\":0,\".relationships .items-list\":0}"},"_document-sheet-registrar":{"type":"person"},"journal-backlinks":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_6nu2k3j5j03","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar Lore#/CF_SEP/Lhazaar Principalities#/CF_SEP/02.09.12. People#/CF_SEP/Potential Crew","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"FDTdQ6D3sO3V4tDz","name":"Master Scourge","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Master Scourge is the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> boatswain and master-at-arms, and Mr. Lagraa’s right-hand man. As boatswain, he is in charge of all activities and sailors on deck, and as master-at-arms, he is responsible for discipline. Master Scourge is a sneering man with a braided beard and a mouth full of gold teeth. His body is tall and thin, and even his long coat and heavy boots fail to give any impression of strength or bulk. A sadistic coward, Scourge uses his association with Lagraa as protection and in return has no morals when it comes to the tasks his master sets. He is bold and violent when the odds are stacked in his favor, happily kicking a dying dog in the street if asked to do so. But should that dog get up and bite, he quickly f lees.</p>\n<p>Master Scourge is a key villain in the early part of the adventure, and his whispered words further poison Mr. Lagraa against the PCs. Scourge’s relationship with the PCs is a crucial one. He immediately senses something out of the ordinary about them, and his dreams of rank and fortune soon begin to unravel. Like most bullies, Scourge is a coward at heart, and sets out to discredit and ultimately kill his rivals.</p>\n<p>This enmity is personal, and primarily directed at a single PC, though how this manifests is ultimately up to you. Scourge was recently rejected by Sandara Quinn (see page 56), and any object of her affections is sure to earn his jealousy and hatred. Likewise, Scourge might be jealous of a handsome and talented PC and fear for his own position on the ship. While Scourge focuses his hostility on one PC, he is also happy to intimidate and victimize the other PCs, as well as seeking to discredit the PCs’ friends. He avoids the PCs as a group, however, and immediately goes to Lagraa’s side if threatened. If actually attacked, he also goes to Lagraa, who may have the PCs disciplined.</p>\n<p>Playing the bully requires you to temper the PCs’ anger while ensuring they recognize Scourge as a deadly enemy with far too many allies to simply be killed. Terrified as he is of Prince Rockface and having no desire to be keelhauled, Scourge won’t try to kill the PCs—at least, not at first. Instead, he seeks to poison the other crew members against the PCs, and is likely to succeed with his own small band of admirers, whom the PCs will find hard to convert. In essence, this group becomes a rival adventuring party, but with one crucial difference: these rivals also enjoy the support of Mr. Lagraa. It’s not until events move on to the Man’s Promise in Part Two that Lagraa and Scourge decide to have done with the PCs, but they’ll eventually get their comeuppance at the hands of the PCs in Part Three.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"base","_viewcount":5,"role":"Boatswain and Master-at-Arms","location":"The Wormwood","race":"Half-orc","gender":"","age":"","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":{"notes":"Master Scourge is the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> boatswain and master-at-arms, and Mr. Dabrak’s right-hand man. As boatswain, he is in charge of all activities and sailors on deck, and as master-at-arms, he is responsible for discipline. Master Scourge is a sneering man with a braided beard and a mouth full of gold teeth. His body is tall and thin, and even his long coat and heavy boots fail to give any impression of strength or bulk. A sadistic coward, Scourge uses his association with Dabrak as protection and in return has no morals when it comes to the tasks his master sets. He is bold and violent when