ey’ll eventually get their comeuppance at the hands of the PCs in Part Three."},"scrollPos":"{\".description\":50}"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_rxb9n4yk7i","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Crew of the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"},"_document-sheet-registrar":{"type":"base"}}}
{"_id":"FDc8OuXwl18j9XWe","name":"A Pirate's Day","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">A Pirate's Day</h1>\n<p>The <em>Storm Reaver </em>works on discipline and routine. Prince Rockface's philosophy is that a busy swab is a tired swab, and tired swabs don’t pick fights with each other. After breakfast, the crew work at their allotted jobs until dusk, when they gather on the main deck to witness punishments (the “Bloody Hour”), eat dinner, and receive their rum rations. After punishment time and the evening meal, the crew can do what they wish until dawn bell the next morning. </p>\n<p>Each day, the heroes are assigned tasks to complete, based on the their jobs (cook’s mate, rigger, or swab).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tables.Cook's Mate Tasks]{Cook's Mate Tasks}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tables.Rigging Tasks]{Rigging Tasks}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tables.Swab Tasks]{Swab Tasks}</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Each task represents a day’s hard work and requires at least one successful skill check to complete. Failing a task’s required skill check results in punishment. The punishment for failing a check is merely a severe verbal reprimand, or at worse, a @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Punishments]{rope bash}. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} results in @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Punishments]{three lashes}. The number of lashes increases to six if this is the second such failure in a row, to nine lashes for three failures in a row, and so on.</p>\n<p>Work takes place under the watchful eyes of @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Mister Lagraa]{Mr. Lagraa} and @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Master Scourge]{Master Scourge}, and getting away from them is not easy. If a hero refuses to work or is unable to work, she receives a @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Punishments]{dozen lashes} for the first such offense and a dozen lashes with the cat for the second. A third offense results in the character being put in the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Punishments]{sweatbox} for 12 hours.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_lasttab":"description","scrollPos":"{\".description\":0}"},"cf":{"id":"temp_uib0igo50md","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"GOOUifvBeOF8x8qZ","name":"Galley","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Galley</h1>\n<p>The galley is the domain of Krornik “Fishguts” Kragshard, the drunken ship’s cook. The cramped and chaotic kitchen holds two wooden worktables, several wooden cupboards, and two small stoves against the port wall, as well as virtually every cooking utensil imaginable and a frightening array of meat cleavers. The kitchen is a madness of dirt, food, and knives, and finding anything in here requires a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} check. The stoves are perpetually lit, and large cauldrons bubble away atop them all times. A huge array of spices mingle with barrels of rainwater, two tuns of rum, cupboards full of ship’s biscuit and salted beef, barrels of sauerkraut, and a small supply of fresh vegetables picked up in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport}. Despite the chaos, the entire galley functions as a set of masterwork @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Cook's Utensils]{Cook's Utensils} for cooking checks.</p>\n<h3>Valuable Items Lost</h3>\n<p>Several items of value are lost among the ruin and squalor in the galley, each requiring a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} check to discover: a masterwork dagger being used as a butcher’s knife, a pair of handaxes used as meat cleavers, 11 knives, a short sword, a vial of holy water, a good lock hanging unused off a pantry cupboard, 2 pounds of soap, four waterskins, a barrel of poor wine, six bottles of good karrnathi brandy worth 20 gp each, three bottles of magnificent rum worth 12 gp each, a large cookbook worth 125 gp (using the tome while cooking grants a +1 bonus on cooking checks), a prosthetic leg made of wood and edged with a silver band worth 45 gp, and 12 sp fallen behind a cupboard. In addition, a trio of harpoons, a spear, and Kroop’s steadfast grapple hang on the walls.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L91WkUzg75E8tVjM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dljw0qnmnui","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Locations on the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"GcEoK3nB0buKm7FB","name":"Davin Korran","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>(m human, early 20s). Davin and Daina met in High Walls. The young man from Seaside had been training as an artificer before escaping Cyre, and in High Walls, he was always helping people repair things whenever he could procure materials to do so. (Davin is more of a magewright than an artificer due to his stunted training, limited magical abilities and good with his hands.) He had been separated from his parents and sister during the chaos of escaping Cyre and has little hope that they survived, and when Daina asked him to come to New Cyre with her and Torlan, he wanted to, but decided to stay in High Walls in the hopes that his family might one day show up.</p>\n<p>Daina last heard from him in late 996 when she received a letter shortly before leaving for the Principalities. At the time, he was still in High Walls holding out hope that his parents and sister were still alive and would find him there.</p>\n</div>","img":"modules/monks-enhanced-journal/assets/person.png","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"person","relationships":[{"type":"place","id":"J9z3O8X8KvWKhjmM","relationship":"Last Known Residence","hidden":false}],"role":"","location":"High Walls, Sharn","race":"Human","gender":"Male","age":"23","pronoun":"He/Him","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"Artificer","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","_lasttab":"details","scrollPos":"{\".tab.details .tab-inner\":0,\".tab.description .tab-inner\":0,\".relationships .items-list\":0}","fields":{"race":{"value":true},"gender":{"value":true},"age":{"value":true},"eyes":{"value":true},"skin":{"value":false},"hair":{"value":true},"pronoun":{"value":true},"profession":{"value":true},"voice":{"value":true},"faction":{"value":false},"height":{"value":false},"weight":{"value":false},"traits":{"value":true},"ideals":{"value":false},"bonds":{"value":false},"flaws":{"value":true},"longterm":{"value":false},"shortterm":{"value":false},"beliefs":{"value":false},"secret":{"value":false}}},"_document-sheet-registrar":{"type":"person"},"journal-backlinks":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_6nu2k3j5j03","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar Lore#/CF_SEP/Lhazaar Principalities#/CF_SEP/02.09.12. People#/CF_SEP/Potential Crew","color":"#000000"}}}
