{"_id":"LoWDY9I9n6WDrYUD","name":"Alanto","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Another Cyran PoW in the dungeons of Karrnath. During the two years or so of their joint stay, it was Alanto who convinced Rus that there was no going back to Cyre. No pension awaiting him. But out in Lhazaar, there is potential. Or at least, work. Alanto has some distant family out there, in Tantamar, and Rus should join him if they ever get out.</p>\n</div>","img":"modules/monks-enhanced-journal/assets/person.png","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"person","role":"","location":"Tantamar","race":"","gender":"","age":"","pronoun":"","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","scrollPos":"{\".tab.details .tab-inner\":0,\".tab.description .tab-inner\":0,\".relationships .items-list\":0}","relationships":[{"id":"jD9VwVKBwJ2p0vUg","type":"place","hidden":false,"relationship":"Last Known place of residence"},{"id":"cD2iHikSpmmCPimk","hidden":false}],"_lasttab":"description"},"_document-sheet-registrar":{"type":"person"},"journal-backlinks":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_6nu2k3j5j03","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar Lore#/CF_SEP/Lhazaar Principalities#/CF_SEP/02.09.12. People#/CF_SEP/Potential Crew","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"LpGqZGu7yOfyWh44","name":"Kythri Whirlpool","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Kythri Whirlpool</h1>\n<p>The heroes spy a ship fighting for its life at the edge of a raging whirlpool that suddenly appears in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Manifest Zones]{manifest zone} of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Kythri]. Somehow the crew was able anchor some ropes tp nearby rocks, but their efforts are certainly doomed—unless they can get help. If another ship latches on to the first, it can be pulled free. This is risky, however, as the rescuer may well be pulled into the whirlpool as well.</p>\n<aside class=\"read-aloud\">\n<p>From the crow’s nest comes “Ahoy! Ship off the starboard bow!” Sure enough, there’s a double-master a few hundred yards off, bobbing up and down as if on a string. The lookout peers through his spyglass. “Whirlpool!”</p>\n</aside>\n<h2>The <em>Gladiator</em></h2>\n<p>The ship is the <em>Gladiator</em>, a frigate scavenging the waters nearby. She's captained by a Lhazaar by the name of Mauriana Balich.</p>\n<p>The whirlpool sprang up suddenly as well as the rocks—as they sometimes do in a Kythri manifest zone—and has nearly sucked the <em>Gladiator</em> into her depths. Fortunately, due to quick thinking, the ship used a few of it's ballista to lash heavy ropes to some nearby rocks and staved off certain doom—for the moment.</p>\n<p>The ship’s crew motions frantically when they see the mourners’ vessel, and perhaps even touch off aerial sparks to ensure they’ve captured her attention.</p>\n<h2>Good Samaritans</h2>\n<p>Saving the <em>Gladiator</em> is a Dramatic Task. This is a difficult @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dramatic Tasks]{dramatic task}.</p>\n<p><strong>First Round</strong></p>\n<p>On the first round @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating] rolls can be made to get close enough to the <em>Gladiator</em> without risking the mourner's ship. These rolls should be made at –1. Additionally at least one mourner must make rolls to attach the mourner's ship to the <em>Gladiator</em> with the anchor coils. This would require flying rolls or a swimming (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]) rolls at a –4. Failure on swimming rolls will result in the mourner suffering @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue] and being drawn towards the whirlpool.</p>\n<p><strong>Second And Third Round</strong></p>\n<p>With tow-lines attached @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating] rolls can be made at a –2 to pull the frigate free. Failures pull both ships closer to the whirlpool.</p>\n<p>The <em>Gladiator's</em> makeshift moorings break 15 minutes after its would-be rescuers arrive.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong></p>\n<p>Should the Dramatic Task fail then both ships are drawn into the whirlpool and sucked into the plane of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Kythri] for futher adventures.</p>\n<h2>Treasure</h2>\n<p>If the <em>Gladiator</em> is rescued, Captain Balich thanks her saviors with a most amazing gift—thanks his saviors with a most amazing gift—a magical ship’s wheel made from the bones of some mysterious beast. A vessel with the wheel adds +2 to its Handling.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_slwk1t4xhcl","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Savage Tales","color":"#000000"}}}
