{"_id":"M8psGt43gogLJPSh","name":"Plot Point Campaign","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Plot Point Campaign</h1>\n<h2>Threads</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>One of the ships that they find and raid has the name of some cyrans carved into it. It was Squibbed at some point.</li>\n<li>Mention Tidewater Rock</li>\n<li>Mention the Council of Princes</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Twists</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Run an encounter with Tidewater rock. IF the party does not come to an accord with the noble of Tidewater. Have tidewater rock attacked by another pirate ship or get afflicted by undead.</li>\n<li>Have a Cyran Noble come to them to enlist thier services to find a home land for Cyrans.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Plot Points</h2>\n<h3>Season 1: Mutiny against the Cloudreavers</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Welcome to the Storm Reaver:</strong> The scoundrals start with an evening in Port Verge. Wake up press ganged in the <em>Storm Reaver</em>. Are assigned roles, and then watch a good keelhauling. <em>Day 1 from The Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>Day in the life of a pirate: </strong>The scoundrals are bullied by some crew sent my Master Scourge. A few days later they are sent to deal with the bilges. A brawl with owlbear. <em>Day 2, Day4, and Day 5 from The Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>Storm at Sea:</strong> The scoundrals have to survive a storm at sea on the <em>Storm Reaver</em>. <em>Day 8 from the Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>Pirate Duties:</strong> The scoundrals have a few series of encounters. Gathering some crabs for the captain. Training for boarding. Unpleasant duties and attack in the bilges. <em>Day 11, day 14, Day 17, and Day 19 from the Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Man's Promise:</strong> The crew of the <em>Storm Reaver</em> attacks and takes over the Man's Promise. The scoundrals are assigned to the skeleton crew. <em>Day 20 and 21 from the Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>Whisper's of Mutiny:</strong> Things go grim for the Man's Promise crew. The ship is caught in a Storm and shipwrecked. <em>Day 1 to 5 from the Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>Bonewrack Isle:</strong> Exploring Bonewrack Isle and rescue crew members from the grindylows. <em>Bonewrack Isle from the Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>Mutiny!:</strong> The scoundrals mutiny against Mister Dabrak and take over the Man's Promise. <em>Mutiny from the Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Season 2: In the Name of Cyre...</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Hiding the Evidence!:</strong> The scoundrals take the Man's Promise to Rickety' Squibs to disguise their ship and recristen it. <em>Hiding the Evidence from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Landlubber Trap:</strong> The scoundrals encounter a ship that has been set as a trap by Sauaghin. <em>Event 11: Hook, Line, and Sinkerfrom Piracy on the Fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Cracking Tidewater Rock:</strong> The scoundrals find a base of operations by gaining control of Tidewater Rock. <em>Tidewater Rock from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Raid on the Rock:</strong> (Required Landlubber Trap) The scoundrals find a base of operations by gaining control of Tidewater Rock. (perhaps use Attack on Brigandy Bay pg 147 for some ideas on how to conduct the fight) <em>Combined Event 16 and 17 from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Treasure Hunting in Mancatching Cove:</strong> The scoundrals sail to mancatcher cove and battle the Sahuaghin there to gain the treasure that has been left there. <em>The Treasure of Mancatacher Cove from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Savage Tales</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Sea Wolves:</strong> The scoundrals commit an act of priacy on the hazaar Seas. <em>Event 7 from Piracy on the fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Raiding Settlements:</strong> The scoundrals may commit land raids on sea-side settlements. <em>Event 8: Low-Hanging Fruit from Piracy on the fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Upon the Famished Mane:</strong> The scoundrals encounter a pirate ship being burned by a Karrnathi warship. <em>Event 10: Upon the Famished Mane from Piracy on the Fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>No Honor Among Thieves:</strong> This savage tale occurs as the scoundrals come upon an attack by another pirate ship already underway. The PCs first sight the battle from a mile away and come upon it just as the pirates have disabled the merchant ship and now prepare to board her. <em>Event 13: No Honor Among Thieves from Piracy on the Fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Frying Pan:</strong> The scoundrals encounter a Karrn or Brelish pirate hunter. <em>Event 13: The Frying Pan from Piracy on the Fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>For Whom the Bell Tolls:</strong> This savage tale takes place over three successive nights when the scoundrals are out of sight of the nearest shore. It always occurs in the waning hours of the day as the sun sinks below the horizon, as they are stalked and attacked by a ghost ship. <em>Event 14: For Whom the Bell Tolls from Piracy on the Fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Hijack the Immortal:</strong> The scoundrals are highered by someone to hijack a powerful warship. <em>Hijack the Immortal pg 140 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>Debauchery:</strong> The scoundrals are approached by a vengeful father to assassinate someone who has defiled his daughter. <em>Debauchery pg 141 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Terror:</strong> Can the scoundrals rescue a unwilling shipwright from service on Prince Rhygers secret vessel. <em>The Terror pg 151 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>Treasure for the Taking:</strong> The scoundrals are lead to some buried treasure by Stumpy Pete (Stumpy Pete perhaps works at Rickety Squibs). <em>Treasure for the Taking pg 154 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Low Down:</strong> The scoundrals find a dinghy at seas, they rescue one of the most ruthless pirates in the Lhazaar Seas. <em>The Low Down pg 156 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Butcher:</strong> (Requires The Low Down) The scoundrals find a ship with sailors horribly butchered. If they set off in persuit they find the man they rescued. What will the scoundrals do? <em>The Butcher pg 156 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>Big for Freedom:</strong> The scoundrals are asked to save a salve girl serving at a tavern in a port town? <em>Bid for Freedom pg 160 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>Revenge:</strong> (Could be used to turn against the Seadragons??) When the scoundrals try to sell some treasure, and item is noticed by a heartbroken lover. He asks for help with revenge? <em>Revenge pg 173 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Dragonshard Ship:</strong> The scoundrals are asked to help a fellow pirate with some piracy, but find it better guarded than thought. <em>The Iron Ship pg 173 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>False Kidnapping:</strong> The scoundrals are asked by a noble to stage a fake kidnapping. This a noble tale to help save a daughter from a poor marriage. <em>False Kidnapping pg 176 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Black Prince:</strong> The scoundrals are asked by a ghost to help put him to rest. <em>The Black Prince pg 177 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>A Toast to Death:</strong> The scoundrals are tasked with smuggling wine to on of the princes. Unknown to them the wine is poisoned. Use this Savage Tale to frame the party and create bad relations with other pirates.  <em>A Toast to Death pg 173 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Encounters</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Night Swimmers:</strong> During the evening the ship is attacked by a group of Sahuaghin. <em>Event 6 include from Piracy on the Fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Wreck of the Carcanus:</strong> Use as a idea for the scounrals aquiring magical sails for their ship. <em>Wreck of Carcanus pg 150 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n</ul>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":7},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_bmn52t4oyo","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar","color":"#618ba1"}}}
{"_id":"MfxQEJpAFYnCf2JW","name":"Krornik \"Fishguts\" Kragshard","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Most people think Krornik “Fishguts” Kragshard gets his nickname from the stains on his apron or the contents of his infamous stew, but few know he earned the sobriquet as a competitive eater in the low bars of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport}. As a young man, it was said that Kragshard could eat more of anything, and faster, than anyone. Folks still talk about the night that Kragshard devoured an entire bucket of boiled eggs in the Salty Swab by the docks.</p>\n<p>Kragshard was trained as a professional chef at the Lobster’s Armor, one of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport}’s most popular (and expensive) restaurants, but when he was thrown out for inappropriate behavior with his assistant, he ended up plying his trade with several sailing vessels in the Lhazaar before embarking on Captain Rockface’s <em>Storm Reaver</em>, where he has served as ship’s cook for the past 3 years.</p>\n<p>An affable fellow, Kragshard loves his food, and has more recently developed a taste for rum, a habit that’s only encouraged by Cut-Throat Grok, the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> quartermaster and Kragshard’s best friend aboard the ship.</p>\n<p>Sadly for Kragshard, his drinking led him to bet his own life against Prince Rockface in a card game one drunken night 2 years ago. Kragshard lost, and his life became Rockface’s to do with what he would. Rockface now thinks as little of Kragshard as he does a bilge rat, but he’s not yet killed the cook because drunk as he is, Kragshard is still a better cook than anyone else on the <em>Storm Reaver</em>, and the captain is partial to his cooking.</p>\n<p>Kragshard’s days begin with blearily handing out ship’s biscuits to the crew on deck before retiring to the galley to prepare the evening meal (almost always fish stew) in a big pot. Then he cozies up with a bottle of rum (sometimes mixed with raw eggs) and waits for the rest of the day to pass. Nevertheless, Kragshard is a skilled chef, though few of the crew beyond the captain and his officers ever get the chance to sample Kragshard’s more palatable fare.</p>\n<p>His only joy, aside from drinking and swapping yarns with Grok, are his chickens. Kragshard loves his poultry and collects any rare breeds he comes across. Anyone with a background in farming finds Kragshard friendly, while those who truly know their birds quickly discover a helpful friend. Kragshard’s favorite bird, a large black cockerel named Black-Hearted Bezebel, often perches on the cook’s shoulder and even talks to him, or so Kragshard occasionally drunkenly claims.</p>\n<h3>Appearance</h3>\n<p>Kragshard is a large, some would say fat, man, weighing well over 200 pounds and standing only 5 feet tall. He exudes an air of neglect, perhaps even despair, from the bushy tufts of black hair behind his ears, to his rotting teeth, to the stains on his filthy apron. He walks with a wallowing waddle, particularly when drunk, but is capable of surprising acts of strength. Kragshard talks with a thick Shackles accent, which some people find hard to follow. He’s had so many lashes that his back is like tanned leather, and he claims to not even feel the bite of the lash anymore. After 44 years in the school of hard knocks, Kragshard is a man who clearly cares little for himself or what people think of him. Nevertheless, he is at heart a kind man, and does his best to protect his cook’s mate from punishments brought on by mistakes made by either of them.</p>\n<h3>Gossip</h3>\n<p>The PCs can learn the following about Kragshard with successful Diplomacy checks to gather information.</p>\n<p>DC 5: “Fishguts” might once have been a famous chef at that fancy place in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport}, but now all he cooks is fishgut stew. He’s so pickled in rum now, bilgewater is all he can make.</p>\n<p>DC 10: Remember the last cook’s mate? Nobody does—only when he disappeared. Just up and vanished, that one, like he was spirited away, or maybe dropped in a pot...</p>\n<p>DC 15: Kragshard was so drunk once that he bet his life in a game with the captain, and now he’s little more than Rockface’s slave.</p>\n<h3>CampaiGn Role</h3>\n<p>Krornik Kragshard begins the adventure as a cynical, washed up drunk who is insensibly intoxicated half of the time, dreaming of a better life. However, he is also an obvious potential friend and ally of the PCs, as he loathes the captain and crew of the <em>Storm Reaver</em> and longs for a chance to escape. Kragshard makes an excellent NPC to plant the idea of mutiny in the PCs’ minds. He is not a risktaker, however, and can, like Sandara Quinn (see page 56), act as a voice of reason as the PCs plan their actions. If the PCs manage to befriend Kragshard, he can become a useful ally for the PCs in the future. Besides being a fine cook, he has handy communication skills and can also help out in a fight if needed. Kragshard has also plied his trade in the Shackles throughout his life and has an excellent knowledge of the region and its perils, personalities, and possibilities.</p>\n<p>As the adventure progresses, Kragshard’s interactions with the PCs begin to give his life purpose, to the extent that by the time the PCs move to the Man’s Promise in Part Two, he begins drinking much less. Away from the sour atmosphere of the <em>Storm Reaver</em>, Kragshard’s spirits lighten, and he is only drunk 1 day in every four. When the PCs finally mutiny, Kragshard is sober for the event, and aids the PCs as best he can. If the mutiny is successful, Kragshard announces that his new friends have inspired him to turn over a new leaf. If the PCs are cutthroats, Kragshard throws his lot in with them to begin a new life. If they are kindhearted dandies, Kragshard sees in them a more honorable way of life. Regardless, he offers his services as ship’s cook to the PCs. His lapses into drinking become less frequent—he is now drunk only 1 day in every week—and continue to be so throughout the rest of the Adventure Path.</p>\n<p>It is unlikely that the PCs will make an enemy of Kragshard, but should they do so, he gladly assists anyone who wants to kill the PCs. Having had a taste of possible freedom, he wants to punish those who let him taste it before he crawls back into the bottom of a rum bottle to die.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/krornik-kragshard.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"person","_viewcount":3,"role":"","location":"Majestic Griffon","race":"Dwarf","gender":"Male","age":"178","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"Ship's Cook","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":{"notes":""},"scrollPos":"{\".tab.details .tab-inner\":0,\".tab.description .tab-inner\":0,\".relationships .items-list\":0}","relationships":[],"pronoun":"He/Him","_lasttab":"description","fields":{"race":{"value":true},"gender":{"value":true},"age":{"value":true},"eyes":{"value":true},"skin":{"value":false},"hair":{"value":true},"pronoun":{"value":true},"profession":{"value":true},"voice":{"value":true},"faction":{"value":false},"height":{"value":false},"weight":{"value":false},"traits":{"value":true},"ideals":{"value":false},"bonds":{"value":false},"flaws":{"value":true},"longterm":{"value":true},"shortterm":{"value":true},"beliefs":{"value":true},"secret":{"value":true}}},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgiu42x0xnj","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar Lore#/CF_SEP/Lhazaar Principalities#/CF_SEP/02.09.12. People#/CF_SEP/Ship's Crew","color":"#000000"},"_document-sheet-registrar":{"type":"person"},"journal-b