{"_id":"Sc8zngwHZvU5mmmY","name":"Boarding School","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Boarding School</h1>\n<p> </p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"quick-encounters":{"quickEncounter":"{\"journalEntryId\":\"MMMTZcygBDdHuIMw\",\"extractedActors\":[{\"numActors\":1,\"dataPackName\":\"savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary\",\"actorID\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"name\":\" Krornik Kragshard\",\"savedTokensData\":[],\"generatedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}],\"combinedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}]}],\"hideQE\":true,\"qeVersion\":\"0.8.4\"}"},"cf":{"id":"temp_72m1iiovqki","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver Savage Tales","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"TFDAsNf5ym4DG8jL","name":"The Butcher","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">The Butcher</h1>\n<section class=\"secret gm-secret\">\n<p>Ideally, several months should pass between this adventure and the events of The Low Down.</p>\n</section>\n<p>The heroes spy a frigate drifting in the wind, her masts smashed and sails tattered. Drawing near, the group sees signs of a recent and bloody battle—several large holes are clearly visible in her side and corpses litter the splintered, bloodsoaked deck.</p>\n<p>As the heroes watch, a lone figure staggers onto the deck from the rear cabins. Spying them, the figure tries to reach the side of ship, waving frantically as he lurches forward. He barely makes half a dozen steps before he falls lifeless to the planks.</p>\n<p>On boarding, the heroes discover a scene of absolute carnage. A successful Common Knowledge roll reveals most of the injuries were not inflicted in battle. Most of the corpses have been horribly mutilated in some way. Characters failing a Fear check are violently sick and gain a level of Fatigue which is only recovered 30 minutes after leaving the Conquistador.</p>\n<h2>The Survivor</h2>\n<p>The survivor is unconscious and badly bleeding. Both of his hands have been severed at the wrists and his nose has been hacked off. A successful Healing roll staunches the blood flow and returns the man to consciousness. Once awake, he tells his tale.</p>\n<section class=\"read-aloud\">\n<p>“My name is Jim Black, ship’s cook. Pirates attacked us barely two hours ago. Having no escort, the captain saw fit to surrender, planning on trading the cargo for our lives. He assembled us on the deck and raised a flag of surrender. The swines raked the deck with grapeshot before boarding.</p>\n<p>“The captain offered his cargo without a struggle but the pirate captain shot him on the spot. They took the cargo but they had no intention of letting us live. The pirate captain had every man butchered—gutted some, amputated limbs off others, and even made some of them eat their own body parts.</p>\n<p>“That devil hacked off my nose and tried to make me eat it. I put on a brave face, hoping he’d show mercy if I didn’t beg, and said it needed pepper. He asked my trade, and when I told him he hacked my hands off and left me here to die. What use am I now with no hands, eh? There’s still cargo below if you want it—I’m not going to put up a fight.”</p>\n</section>\n<p>Jim describes the pirate captain. Any character who took part in  The Low Down (157) and makes a Common Knowledge roll recognizes the man as the mariner they rescued. Jim adds that the pirate ship was a galleon called the Mad Dog and it sailed away east.</p>\n<p>Below deck are two cargo spaces worth of food—Low’s ship lacked room to store the entire cargo.</p>\n<h2>Hunting the Mad Dog</h2>\n<p>If the heroes decline the cargo and set off immediately, the Mad Dog has a three-hour lead. Taking the Conquistador’s cargo increases the lead to six hours. How much head start Low has is irrelevant—but don’t tell the group.</p>\n<p>Believing the Conquistador’s crew to be dead, Low is in no rush to escape. Riding hard with the wind, the heroes spy a sail on the horizon shortly before dusk. Use the standard Chase rules. When the ships draw level, Low recognizes the heroes as his rescuers and shouts across to them.</p>\n<section class=\"read-aloud\">\n<p>“Well strike me down! I never thought I’d see you fine chaps again. I have no beef with you lads—you did get me a good turn and that’s a rare thing. I’ll return the favor now—turn sail and run ‘n I’ll let you go in peace. Continue your present course and I’ll watch you eat your own lips as you beg for mercy.”</p>\n</section>\n<p>Low will actually let the heroes sail away in peace if they choose to turn around. Should they cross his path a second time he has no hesitation about killing them—he considers the favor repaid in full. Of course, he’ll also take great delight in boarding their ship and cutting off their lips if they try to slug it out.</p>\n<p>If the group loses the fight and surrenders, Low does indeed cut off their lips, as well as their ears and noses—each character gains the Ugly Hindrance—before letting them go as a warning to others.</p>\n<h3>The Mad Dog (Galleon)</h3>\n<p>Acc/Top Speed: 2/12; Travel Speed: 3; Handling: –3; Toughness: 20(4); Crew: 30+40; Cargo Space: 6; Guns: 20 Notes: Heavy Armor; Low has sacrificed cargo space for additional cannons.</p>\n<p>Pirates (65): 60 Pirates and five Veteran Pirate officers (p. 195).</p>\n<p>Booty: A King’s Ransom aboard the Mad Dog. Among the treasure is a golden triangle engraved with unintelligible writing. The hold contains four units of food and two units of gunpowder.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_4s6bxi84dvu","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Savage Tales#/CF_SEP/The Dragonshards","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"THD1DJO5MoO1VXKm","name":"Flora Aarland","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Rus meeet her when he spent some time at a rehabilitation ranch and wildlife preserve in 989 YK.</p>\n</div>","img":"modules/monks-enhanced-journal/assets/person.png","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"person","relationships":[],"scrollPos":"{\".tab.details .tab-inner\":0,\".tab.description .tab-inner\":0,\".relationships .items-list\":0}","role":"","location":"","race":"","gender":"","age":"","pronoun":"","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":""},"_document-sheet-registrar":{"type":"person"},"journal-backlinks":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_6nu2k3j5j03","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar Lore#/CF_SEP/Lhazaar Principalities#/CF_SEP/02.09.12. People#/CF_SEP/Potential Crew","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"TvZyPlpUJTktweHi","name":"Night Swimmers","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Night Swimmers</h1>\n<p>This event occurs shortly after the PCs have departed Rickety’s Squibs in their newly squibbed ship. The encounter should occur when the PCs’ ship is in the open ocean shortly before eight bells, the end of the late-night watch and the beginning of the morning watch (about 4 a.m.).</p>\n<p>Creatures: Three sahuagin, members of the tribe that dwells in Mancatcher Cove, have been sent to reconnoiter the Fever Sea and to prey upon lone ships that can be surprised. They clamber onto deck and attempt to silently murder any sailors on watch before slipping back overboard with their victims in tow. If the PCs are on watch, allow Perception checks to detect the sahuagin’s stealthy boarding party before they attack. Otherwise, or unless the PCs have posted more than two sailors on watch or taken other unusual precautions, assume that the raid is successful and goes unnoticed until the next watch comes on deck and finds only a few bloodstains. A DC 17 Survival check reveals a few wet prints in the shape of a webbed and clawed humanoid foot, which PCs who succeed at a DC 15 Knowledge (nature) can identify as the tracks of sahuagin.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Sahuagin] (3):</span> If two sahuagin are killed, the survivor leaps overboard and flees. If a sahuagin is in danger of being captured alive, it swallows a puffer fish spine hidden in its mouth, causing it to choke to death on the toxin and preventing it from revealing anything about its tribe.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_slwk1t4xhcl","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Savage Tales","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"U6QtUVBcJ3kCOUrn","name":"02 Life Aboard the Storm Reaver","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Life Aboard the Storm Reaver</h1>\n<p>Each day aboard the Storm Reaver the swabs will be assigned a task from their corresponding task list as outlined in @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.A Pirate's Day]{A Pirate's Day}. The swabs will be allowed @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Board Actions]{Ship Board Actions} one per day and one per night as outlined in those rules.</p>\n<p>Each day consists of</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Wake up</li>\n<li>Ship tack for breakfast</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.A Pirate's Day]{Daily assignments}</li>\n<li>Possible @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Board Actions]{daily ship action}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Punishments]{Bloody Hour}</li>\n<li>Evening @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Grog Ration]{Grog Ration} and evening meal</li>\n<li>Possible @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Board Actions]{nightly ship action}</li>\n<li>Bedtime and/or further @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Board Actions]{nightly ship action}</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>As Time Goes By</h2>\n<p>The following events should be played approxiately around these days:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Day 2: @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Laying Down the Law]{Laying Down the Law}</li>\n<li>Day 4: @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Something in the Bilges]{Something in the Bilges}</li>\n<li>Day 5: @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Fight with the Owlbear]{Fight with the Owlbear}, heavy rain starts in the evening</li>\n<li>Day 6: Building storm (–1 on all rigging checks for the day)</li>\n<li>Day 7: @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.The Storm on the Storm Reaver]{The Storm on the Storm Reaver}</li>\n<li>Day 8: Weakening storm (–1 on all rigging checks for the day)</li>\n<li>Day 10: @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Trouble in the Sun]{Trouble in the Sun}</li>\n<li>Day 12: @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Boarding School]{Boarding School}</li>\n<li>Day 13 on: Unpleasant Duties. At this point Mr. Lagraa and Master Scourge have had enough of the swabs and from this point forward give the swabs all the shit jobs that they hate the most. Any pirate not at least Friendly with the swabs has thier reaction decreased by one. Mister Lagraa has been completely turned by Master Scourge and makes more appearances and takes more of a focus on the swabs at this point.</li>\n<li>Day 13 and 14: Cold front strikes (–1 on all checks to avoid @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{fatigue})</li>\n<li>Day 15: @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Risky Games in the Bilges]{Risky Games in the Bilges}</li>\n<li>Day 16: @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.03 Attacking the Majestic Griffon]{Attacking the Majestic Griffon}</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Mister Lagraa and Master Scourge</h2>\n<p>Frequent interactions and run-ins should happen mainly with Master Scourge, though Mr. Lagraa should also be made into a villian. But she has more things to occupy her time. Master Scourage might also use some of cronies to also harass the swabs. These might include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Gragoth]{Gragoth}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Patch \"Salty\" Kolkrinun]{Patch \"Salty\" Kolkrinun}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Sador Chumlett]{Sador Chumlett}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Maheem]{Maheem}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Slippery Syl]{Slippery Syl}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Jaundiced Sudak]{Jaundiced Sudak}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Tam \"Narwhal\" Tate]{Tam \"Narwhal\" Tate}</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Experiences to make happen</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Pirates can make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} check to assertain the location of the <em>Storm Reaver</em>. Modifiers depend on the location of the ship.</li>\n<li>Talk to Trucco about his past experience being Press Ganged and the items he might have about getting gear back.</li>\n<li>Have someone run into @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Rosie Cusswell]{Rosie Cusswell} after seeing Grok. She is upset at her inability to get back her Fiddle.</li>\n<li>Crimson Cogs might want to encounter Torlan after his tale the night before.</li>\n<li>Roll every time Daina is in the Galley about what she might find within the Galley on the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tables.Galley Finds]{Galley Finds} table.</li>\n<li>Have someone see @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Hakrilli Quarne]{Hakrilli Quarne} and @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Grovus Stormbread]{Grovus Stormbread} in a strong arguement about the arcane.</li>\n<li>Daina should encounter @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.\"Caulky\" Tarron]{\"Caulky\" Tarron} food tasting, with an opportunity to notice that she might have been at the Tavern the night they where Press ganged.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"quick-encounters":{"quickEncounter":"{\"journalEntryId\":\"MMMTZcygBDdHuIMw\",\"extractedActors\":[{\"numActors\":1,\"dataPackName\":\"savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary\",\"actorID\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"name\":\" Krornik Kragshard\",\"savedTokensData\":[],\"generatedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}],\"combinedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}]}],\"hideQE\":true,\"qeVersion\":\"0.8.4\"}"},"cf":{"id":"temp_n10pg472em","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"UMDOb9ZP73bxRpC9","name":"The Coldest Drake Monster","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">The Coldest Drake Monster</h1>\n<p>In the Undertaker's Brewer is a dwarven stranger with only one arm. If asked, Rikas Talunthun has a harrowing tale to tell.</p>\n<aside class=\"read-aloud\">\n<p>“I was the captain of the Dancing Goose, a drake whaler. We hunted drake turtles off the coast here. We found nothing but a suckling baby in a week. Killed its mother five days later. We were hitching the tow-lines to the carcass when the boat froze under us. There was another one. This was the biggest, meanest turtle I’d ever spied, and I don't know how it created the ice. It had scars all over it—like it’d fought something bigger than it—and won.</p>\n<p>It smashed open the hull from the rear and pushed itself in. Some of the crew tried to fight it but the thing gobbled ‘em up like shrimp.</p>\n<p>It made sure the Dancing Goose was good and smashed before it started bashing the ice around us. Seventeen men slid into the sea, gasping for air in that cold, cold water. Two of ‘em, a pair of warforged, even went below to fight ‘em but they never returned. I lay on a block of ice with my arm half-frozen in the slab. Had to hack it off with my own knife. Then I kicked my way home and ain’t set foot on a ship since.</p>\n<p>That drake ain’t got no special bounty on him, but there’s somethin’ most o’ the locals don’t know. The success of my crew was in no small part to Hastor, my artificer. That beast swallowed hastor whole. On his hand was a magical ring, a relic he used to go beneath the waves like a merfolk. He could go to any depth, stay under for days, and swim like a shark. I’ve cut open a dozen drake turtles and I’ve found trinkets galore in their gizzards. They stick in there, it seems. You find that monster, you’ll find that ring.”</p>\n</aside>\n<p>Finding this specific drake turtle is easier than it might sound—it still lurks near the carcass of its mate where the <em>Dancing Goose </em>went down. A ship in that spot has a 1 in 4 chance per day of encountering the creature. Rikas will guide a ship to the spot for 100 gp and a share of any other treasure found (he doesn’t want the ring).</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Drake Turtle (1):</span> The beast is mostly a Drake Turtle like any other, but with an extra point of Smarts, and Size of 7. Instead of Steam breath it has a cold breath that will freeze colder water like the Norwhale. It’s also vengeful as hell. </li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Treasure</h3>\n<p>Worthwhile level treasure, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Ring of Wave Diving]{Ring of Wave Diving}.</p>\n<p> </p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_slwk1t4xhcl","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Savage Tales","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"Unf9BdNknxxW8NJc","name":"03 Attacking the Majestic Griffon","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Attacking the Majestic Griffon</h1>\n<h3>Ambience</h3>\n<p>Although the swabs have only a relatively small part to play in this fight, try to give your players a cinematic experience of the battle. Describe the noises of fighting that drift out of the mist, which occasionally parts to give the swabs a glimpse of the larger battle. As pirates and sailors fall or are thrown into the sea, let the swabs hear their screams as they’re ripped apart by sharks. Finally, describe the hush that falls over the two ships as the battle finally nears its end.</p>\n<h3>Hold the quarterdeck</h3>\n<p>As the <em>Storm Reaver</em> closes to within half a mile of the <em>Majestic Griffon</em>, Riaris Krine summons the swabs to the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> poop deck to give them their task for the upcoming battle.</p>\n<aside class=\"read-aloud\">\n<p>“The ship’s wheel is on the aft deck, just below the sterncastle. You’re going to grapple over, incapacitate the guards on the sterncastle, take the wheel, and guard the ship’s boats. Stop anyone who tries to get away on one of the boats. Don’t move from the wheel until the fighting’s done, or you’ll have to answer to me. Oh yeah, as we get close, it’s going to get foggy. Just stick to what I told you to do.”</p>\n</aside>\n<p>Krine puts the swab who performed best in the boarding training in charge of the boarding party, and issues any swab who still has not acquired a weapon a single weapon (excluding alchemist’s fire) from the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Officer's Hall and Armory]{armory}.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} check:</strong> The PCs can make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} check to convince Krine of the importance of their mission and choose two other pirates to accompany them, but characters such as Grok, Kroop, and Owlbear are all busy elsewhere. The swabs can choose two hostile or unfriendly NPCs if they wish—people do die in battle after all.</p>\n<h3>The Sea</h3>\n<p>The captain orders Fishguts and the cook's mate to slaughter a pig and throw it overboard to attract sharks for the coming battle.</p>\n<p>If a sailor or pirate falls overboard there is a 1 in 3 chance each round that they are attacked by a Shark. Each time someone is attacked by a shark and but, another shark comes to the prey.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Shark]{Shark} (6)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Closing for Boarding</h3>\n<p>While the <em>Storm Reaver</em> closes for boarding the Arcane Cannon is fired and just before boarding a barrage of ballista's are fired at the prey. The swabs will have up to four rounds worth of actions to fire or cast spells on the other ship before the ships close enough for boarding. Each round there is a 40% chance the swab is attacked by a crossbow. </p>\n<p>After 4 rounds, the two ships collide, and the pirates begin hurling grapples and lowering planks to board the Majestic Griffon. The ships remain locked together until the battle ends.</p>\n<h3>Round 1: Boarding Action</h3>\n<p>The swabs must cross from the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> quarterdeck to the <em>Majestic Griffon's</em> aftcastle. 6 sailors guard the aftcastle plus the pilot.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Sailor]{Sailor} (6)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Pilot]{Pilot} (1)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Round 3: The Prince's Back</h3>\n<p>At this point in the battle the fog parts, allowing the swabs to see Prince Mike Rockface, Riaris Krine, and Gragoth rushing towards the doors leading to the second deck below. Have the swabs make <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}</strong> checks. Those that succeed notice a sailor sneaking up behind Prince Rockface. Any warning will or attack will allow Rockface to turn to slay the sailor. Rockface looks up at the swab that provided any warning and nods in recognition. If the swabs don't warn the Prince, the sailor will strike a non-fatal blow from behind. Once slaying the sailor, Prince Rockface will look around and notices the swabs could have warned her.</p>\n<h3>Round 6: Fleeing Sailors</h3>\n<p>Three sailors appear out of the fog, hoping to release one of the ships boats and flee. They must make two <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}</strong> checks to release the boat and one to jump aboard.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Sailor]{Sailor} (3)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Round 7-10: The Battle Turns</h3>\n<p>Through the fog, the swabs can see the crew scattering or surrendering. Below, Prince Mika momentarily appears, gripping what appears to be a human heart in her hands.</p>\n<h3>Round 11: Abandoning Ship</h3>\n<p>The ships first mate and two sailors appear on the quarterdeck intent on fleeing in one of the ships boats.  Any successes from the prior effort make this easier.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Sailor]{Sailor} (2)</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.First Mate]{First Mate} (1)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Aftermath</h2>\n<p>The battle ends with the pirates victorious. The fog dissipates, and a line of prisoners from the Man’s Promise is paraded before Prince Rockface and the cheering crew of the <em>Storm Reaver</em>.</p>\n<p>Aboard the <em>Storm Reaver</em>, a party begins as the pirates celebrate their victory with fine food and drink from the <em>Majestic Griffon’s</em> hold. Prince Rockface holds a meeting with his top officers and divvies up the plunder from the <em>Majestic Griffon</em> among the crew in the early evening. Bolstered by gold and good drink, the party lasts for 36 hours, well into the next night. Naturally, no work takes place during the party. During this time, the swabs can take up to 5 ship actions of their choice, or do nothing but drink and revel like most of the pirate crew does.</p>\n<p><strong>Treasure:</strong> Each swab receives 150 gp in coinage as his or her share of the booty, modified by the following factors.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>If the swabs took the aft deck and sterncastle within 6 rounds, they receive two @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Potion of Healing, Major]{Potion of Healing, Major} and a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Potion of Invisibility, Minor]{Potion of Invisibility, Minor}, and each is awarded an additional 100 gp.</li>\n<li>If a swab warned Prince Rockface as he was being attacked in Round 3, the swabs receive an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Amulet of Natural Armor, Minor]{Amulet of Natural Armor, Minor}. If the swabs also killed the attacking sailor, they receive a short sword (accurate) as well.</li>\n<li>If the swabs did not warn the captain when he was being attacked, each swab receives only a half share of plunder (75 gp).</li>\n<li>For each sailor captured by the swabs, the swabs receive +25 gp to divide among themselves.</li>\n<li>If the swabs killed the First Mate in Round 11, they receive an additional 100 gp to divide among themselves. This reward increases to 200 gp if the swabs managed to capture the officer alive.</li>\n<li>For each pirate accidentally killed, deduct 150 gp from the party’s reward.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Development:</strong> If any swabs did not take part in the battle and are discovered, they are accused of cowardice and given a dozen lashes with the cat before the plunder is distributed. Such characters forfeit their share of the booty.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"quick-encounters":{"quickEncounter":"{\"journalEntryId\":\"MMMTZcygBDdHuIMw\",\"extractedActors\":[{\"numActors\":1,\"dataPackName\":\"savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary\",\"actorID\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"name\":\" Krornik Kragshard\",\"savedTokensData\":[],\"generatedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}],\"combinedTokensData\":[{\"actorId\":\"KEeR7YOKnWikm2I1\",\"isSavedToken\":false}]}],\"hideQE\":true,\"qeVersion\":\"0.8.4\"}"},"cf":{"id":"temp_n10pg472em","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers","color":"#000000"}}}
