{"_id":"Vih1K90gKmHX1Qsa","name":"Officers Quarters","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Officers Quarters</h1>\n<p>These six cabins are the rooms of the some of the main officers of the Storm Reaver. Therooms are detailed clockwise from the upper left.</p>\n<h3>Officers Lockers</h3>\n<p>There are numerous lockers down here, one for each of the crew. Each locker can be picked with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} check –1. Each locker contains [[/r 20d10]] in sovereigns and [[/r 2d10]] in galifars. Additionally they contain [[/r 1d3+1]] items from the @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tables.Crew Lockers]{Crew Lockers} table. The crew generally refers to this cache as their duffle.</p>\n<h3>Gragoth's Room</h3>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>Mister Lagraa's Room</h3>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>Master Scourge's Room</h3>\n<p>Prince Rockface does not have a strong liking to Master Scourge. As such the Boatswain has been given the smallest officers cabin.</p>\n<h3>Grovus Stormbeard's Room</h3>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>Hakrilli Quarne's Room</h3>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>Riaris Krine's Room</h3>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L91WkUzg75E8tVjM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dljw0qnmnui","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Locations on the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"W1qgHLJx4F2O2uXJ","name":"Captain's Cabin","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Captain's Cabin</h1>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Prince Mika Rockface]{Prince Mika Rockface's} cabin is richly decorated, its walls covered with intricate carvings depicting krakens devouring whales. Portholes along the port and starboard walls allow light to drift in, while to the aft lie windows and a door to a balcony. A bed that can double as a navigational or dining table when the mattress is rolled up sits against the starboard bulkhead with a chest to one side. Rich carpets appoint the floor. A desk is against the port wall with charts, navigational equipment, and writting materials scattered across it. Another chest is to the side of the desk.</p>\n<p>The chests are looked with a good lock (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} check –2). The chest next to the bed contains <span style=\"color:#3598db\">Prince Rockface’s</span> personal possessions, while the chest next to the desk includes various books, personal itesm and a selection of nautical charts (which grant a +1 bonus to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Navigation]{Navigation} checks within the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Lhazaar Principalities]{Lhazaar Principalities}).</p>\n<h3>Captain's Privy and Bath</h3>\n<p>Captain Rockface has her own wash basin, bathtub, and privy.</p>\n<h3>Storage Room</h3>\n<p>The door to the Storage is locked with a superior lock(@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} check –4). The storage room has a collect of weapons and the choice pieces of loot she chooses to take from any plunder.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L91WkUzg75E8tVjM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dljw0qnmnui","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Locations on the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"X825Oau4vi3gVWFl","name":"Bilges","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Bilges</h1>\n<p>The lowest deck of the ship, the bilges are a foul, damp place with thick cobwebs above and 1–2 feet of dark, brackish water that stinks abominably below. A ladder leads up to a trap door that opens in the lower hold (area A10), and a single bilge pump rests near the stern. The bilges can also double double as an extension of the ship’s brig if necessary. There are six sets of manacles bolted to the bulkheads.</p>\n<h3>Treasure</h3>\n<p>A number of discarded crates and boxes packed with straw lie in the bilges, among which can be found a suit of leather armor, heavy mace, morning star, cutlass, and 12 sp.</p>\n<p>In addition, a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} check (–1) turns up the following in the dark waters (one item per successful check): a buckler, a masterwork handaxe, a vial of holy water, a tanglefoot bag, two tindertwigs, and 21 gp.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L91WkUzg75E8tVjM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dljw0qnmnui","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Locations on the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"XAPmPRl4bHbr1Ri6","name":"The Wreck of the Sea Snake","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">The Wreck of the Sea Snake</h1>\n<p>In the Frigid Bitch tavern of Arfk sits a small man with blue skin. Should anyone inquire about his odd pallor, a bartender or serving wench relates that his name is Caleb Candelas, a masaquani sailor. Everyone knows he was on the Arkanaus, a frigate that went down a few miles east a month back. Most of the survivors shipped out soon after for warmer climes, but Candelas stayed on and recently bought a sealsuit. No one knows what happened after that, but he hasn’t left yet.</p>\n<p>If Candelas is approached, he is reluctant to discuss his history unless the group seems reasonably trustworthy (A Persuasion roll at –2, no more than one attempt every 10 minutes). Finally, Candelas spills the beans.</p>\n<p>“Aye. I was aboard the Arkanaus. She was full of gunpowder. Pirates hit her and blew out the back. Men were blasted to bits. I saw one man’s body fly north while his legs went south, still kicking. The Cold Sea ran red that day.</p>\n<p>All that blood must have stirred up the fish. Orcas and norwhales set in on us as the ship went down. The pirates was merciful enough to pick up the survivors. Them they could get to before the fish. Some of my mates joined ‘em. A few of us were set off here.”</p>\n<p>If the party pushes Caleb or asks about the sealsuit, a second Persuasion roll might make Caleb tell the rest of the tale.</p>\n<p>The Arkanaus carried gunpowder and gold. The powder is ruined of course, but the gold still sits there in the icy depths. I tried to get to it but the water is rife with orcas and norwhales. It ain’t a job for one man with the shakes.</p>\n<p>If you’ll give me half the treasure, I’ll tell you exactly where the ship went down. You’ll need sealsuits though, the water around here will kill you in seconds without ‘em, less you’re a grael.”</p>\n<h2>The Wreck</h2>\n<p>Candelas is happy to guide the group to where the ship went down, three miles southeast of Kaja on the Cold Sea. It’s easy to find the Arkanaus’ exact location for it’s about 100 yards due north of a small spire of gray rock called the Finger. As Caleb said, the water here is 60’ deep and infested with orcas and norwhales.</p>\n<p>Anyone using the environmental protection spell is protected from the freezing waters, but all others except grael must have a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-gear.Seal Suit]{seal suit}.</p>\n<p>As Candelas promised, a chest of gold lies in a locked stockroom of the Arkanaus. A few minutes worth of work on the door or its lock opens the way. The chest weighs over 100 pounds and contains a King’s Ransom in various treasures, including one relic (rolled randomly from the Relic Table).</p>\n<h2>Orcas</h2>\n<p>The smell of the sealsuits and the sound of breaking into the storeroom attracts two orcas. These beasts are hungry and quite intelligent, so they’re more than happy to circle the wreck for a while to wait out their prey. They might also try a few nudges against the hull. The orcas are more than capable of busting through the sides of the Arkanaus to get at the tasty morsels within. </p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Killer Whale]{Orcas} (2):</span> Two killer whales roam the area (p. 194).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_slwk1t4xhcl","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Savage Tales","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"XeRyxVGWh28WoBzG","name":"Theft, Pilfering, and Secrecy","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Theft, Pilfering, and Secrecy</h1>\n<p>To perform any action unobserved on a crowded ship use the following guidelines for modifiers to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} rolls.</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li>Attempting a stealthy action in a crowd, such as casting a spell with verbal or somatic components without being noticed: –3 penalty to the roll.</li>\n<li>Attempting a stealthy action where there is a chance of discovery, such as visiting the quartermaster’s store during work, exploring a room during the day, or attempting to open a chest in a room while its occupants are sleeping: –2 penalty to the roll.</li>\n<li>Attempting a stealthy action under cover of a suitable diversion, such as attempting to open lockers when the rest of the crew are working or on deck enjoying themselves: no modifier.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Failure</h3>\n<p>Failing this check means the character attempting the action is merely disturbed and is unable to complete the action. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Critical Failures]{Critical Failure} on the check, the character is caught red-handed by a random crew member, and might be turned over to @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-tales.Ship Roles]{master-at-arms} for discipline.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_f5h8exvluwf","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Ship lore","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"XnKy6uYwlpOoOiu1","name":"Ship Board Actions","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Ship Board Actions</h1>\n<p>In addition to their normal jobs on the ship, the PCs can also utilize their time during the day (and night) to explore the ship, scrounger for gear, interact with their shipmates, or attempt to inf luence NPCs.</p>\n<p>With the PCs potentially scattered across the ship working at their jobs, however, there is a danger that early events in the adventure might focus too much upon the actions of individual characters. Some PCs might have more time on their hands and act accordingly. To avoid this, the PCs’ activities aboard ship—carrying out their assigned tasks; exploring the ship; robbing, bullying, or befriending shipmates; working; or playing—are performed as part of ship actions. These actions reflect the time required to set up or complete an activity, such as gathering enough crew to play a game, scouting out a room to make sure it’s empty, and so on. Remember that even the cook’s mate has a job to do during the day, and ship actions are meant to reflect the available time a PC can carve out from his or her work time without going into too much detail.</p>\n<p>Each hero can normally take two ship actions each day, one during the day and one at night. A hero can also attempt to take up to two additional ship actions during the middle watch in the dead of night (any nighttime ship action marked with an asterisk), but to do so the PC must make a successful @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Vigor} check (–1 for each additional ship action taken) or take a level of  @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} for the next day.</p>\n<p>A list of possible ship actions is presented on the following page. As always, use your judgment as to when these actions are appropriate.</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\">Ship Board Actions</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Daytime Actions</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Work Diligently: </strong>Gain a +1 bonus on any one check for a job's daily task.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Influence: </strong>Make normal checks for a job's daily task and make an attempt to influence a single NPC (skill check based on how it is done).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Sneak: </strong>Make normal checks for a job's daily task. Then make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} check to avoid detection, followed by a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} to briefly explore one area of the ship.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Shop: </strong>Take a –1 penalty on all checks for a job's daily task and visit the quartermaster's store.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Shirk:</strong> Take a –1 penalty on all checks for a job's daily task and take time exploring one area of the ship. Make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} check to avoid detection, followed by a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} to explore one area of the ship.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading centered\">Nightime Actions</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Sleep: </strong>Go to bed early and sleep through the night (automatically recover one level of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Gamble:</strong> Play or gamble on a game of chance.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Entertain:</strong> Make one @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} check to entertain the crew.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Influence:</strong> Attempt to influence a single NPC. (Skill check based on how influencing is done.)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Sneak:</strong> Take time exploring one area of the ship. Make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} check to avoid detection, followed by a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (+1) to explore one area of the ship.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Steal: </strong>Attempt to steal something from a locked door or footlocker. The character must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} roll to avoid being seen as well as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} check.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_uib0igo50md","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"ZY7eT1GESbVaeqgT","name":"Tidewater Rock","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Tidewater Rock</h1>\n<p><strong>Island fortress</strong><br /><strong>Population:</strong> 14</p>\n<p>The keep of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Tidewater Rock]{Tidewater Rock} sits right on the lagoon’s edge, where the water ranges from knee deep to neck deep, with powerful ebb tides and rip currents that can sweep invaders out to sea.</p>\n<p>Although Tidewater Rock remains a secure base and harbor, it does not command the reputation it once did. The current owner of the Rock is Vilina Kessler, widow of the late Saal the Bear. Though Lady Kessler is a competent and formidable figure, without any of her late husband’s ships or network of castles, the Lady of the Rock has fallen upon hard times. Lady Kessler’s forces have been reduced to a small body of loyal guards and a few family retainers whom she employs to eke out a living.</p>\n<section class=\"secret gm-secret\">\n<p>The Rock still commands some treasures—its favorable location, its security, and the late captain’s fabled iron shirt from which he gained his nickname—but it is otherwise remote and at the mercy of what the sea chooses to throw upon its shores.</p>\n</section>\n<h3>History of Tidewater Rock</h3>\n<p>A few centuries ago there was a period of time of increased piracy within the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Lhazaar Principalities]{Lhazaar Principalities}. A lord in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Karrnath]{Karrnath} with strong family ties to the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Lhazaar Principalities]{Lhazaar Principalities} saw a particular island as a strong means to handle the piracy. After discovering a natural harbor on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Windward Isle]{Windward Isle}, Lady Anastro ir' Ondric got a land grant from the crown of Galifar and laid claim to the island. Starting with just one ship and a small encampment on Winward's natural harbor, she set about her work. She was able to build a keep, which was named Tidewater Rock, she began clearing the sea lanes. Little did the king know that Lady Anastro was using this as an opportunity to get rid of competition. From the vantage point atop the Rock , she found she could attack particularly ripe targets while receiving ample warning of hostile ships approaching. So she was able to reduce the piracy on the sea lands while simultanously engaging in her own piracy to expand the keep and her fleet.</p>\n<p>Over time, ir'Ondric's successes both politically and on the seas enabled her to build a sizeable fleet, as well as more strongholds on several different islands in the Fever Sea and lands on the mainland. She became a scourge in the Lhazaar while at the same time keeping enough traffic flowing that the crown was happy. Shortly after claiming the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport} she was assassinated. Ir'Ondric's burgeoning principality fell apart among its squabbling captains. Oydelis Helmworth, first mate of ir'Ordic's flagship, <em>The Immortal Karrn, </em>siezed control of the Rock. Within only a few years, Helmworth became a powerful force in the Principalities, and the legend of Tidewater Rock as both a powerful good luck talisman and an impregnable bastion was born.</p>\n<p>Over the many years since, control of Tidewater Rock has passed from hand to hand, and its strategic location and practical defensibility have enabled its owners to enrich themselves substantially, particularly after the Last War started and the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Lhazaar Principalities]{Lhazaar Principalities} went back to it's old ways. During the middle of the Last War the fleet from Tidewater Rock encountered a major setback in a naval battle with a Karrn fleet, that corresponded with a rise in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Seadragon Principality]{Seadragon Principality}, Tidewater Rock became of less strategic importance and the owners came to be of less prominence.  Yet the age-old axiom of “Good fortune and sure sail await what one can crack the Tidewater Rock” has stood the test of time among the pirates of the Lhazaar and is oft-quoted—if seldom heeded—even today.</p>\n<p>The most recent lord of Tidewater Rock was Saal the Bear, captain of the <em>Vale</em> and three other brigs. Like his predecessors, he held Tidewater Rock as his seat, but controlled a few other small castles on surrounding islands as well.</p>\n<p>Over a decade ago, “The Bear” went to sea with his small fleet in a feud with Prince Kel and was never seen again. Rumor has it that Prince Kel had lured Saal into the edges of the the Gray Tide and ambushed him with the help of a previously unknown ally—one Mike Rockface—and that Saal’s fleet was cut to pieces between the enemy fleets. Other rumors report that ambush was conducted by nothing but ships from the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Gray Tide Principality]{Gray Tide Principality}, using one ship as bait to lure Saal into the Gray Tide. Regardless rumors say \"the Bear\" was last seen on the deck of the crippled and sinking <em>Vale</em> at the mercy of the mists of the Gray Tide.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Prince Rockface took control of several of Saal’s undefended castles. She made an attempt to take the Tidewater Rock as well, only to discover those loyal to Saal's had taken charge of its defenses. Multiple attacks of Prince Rockface have been unsuccessful.</p>\n</section>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/sweb-logo.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":4200000},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_9r4pv5h5ul5","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar Lore#/CF_SEP/Lhazaar Principalities#/CF_SEP/02.09.04. Points of Interest","color":"#cc0000"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1,"scrollPos":"{\".description\":0}"},"_document-sheet-registrar":{}}}
{"_id":"ZkCVPU2FgtudRujy","name":"Fantasy","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Thelanian Tiefling (Satyr?) and Captain of The <em>Hand of Plenty</em>. Primary berth: Tantamar, though usually is floating offshore somewhere.</p>\n<p>Fantasy is herself an adept Diviner. Between her auguries and her experience with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Thelanis] and the Narrative, she is able to construct potent fortunes for those with the coin to pay her.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-bestiary/humanoids/tiefling/demon%20succubus%20witch%20sorcerer%20evil%20chaotic%20seductive.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"person","relationships":[{"id":"x8KEsuvQEOs2afyM","type":"organization","hidden":false,"relationship":"Captain and Propietor"},{"type":"place","id":"jD9VwVKBwJ2p0vUg","relationship":"Primary Berth of Hand of Plenty","hidden":false},{"id":"cD2iHikSpmmCPimk","hidden":false}],"scrollPos":"{\".tab.details .tab-inner\":0,\".tab.description .tab-inner\":0,\".relationships .items-list\":0}","role":"","location":"Hand of Plenty","race":"Tiefling","gender":"Gender Fluid","age":"","pronoun":"They/Them","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","_lasttab":"details","fields":{"race":{"value":true},"gender":{"value":true},"age":{"value":true},"eyes":{"value":true},"skin":{"value":false},"hair":{"value":true},"pronoun":{"value":true},"profession":{"value":false},"voice":{"value":true},"faction":{"value":false},"height":{"value":false},"weight":{"value":false},"traits":{"value":true},"ideals":{"value":false},"bonds":{"value":false},"flaws":{"value":true},"longterm":{"value":true},"shortterm":{"value":true},"beliefs":{"value":true},"secret":{"value":true}}},"_document-sheet-r