{"_id":"mDtxZmFyfuESNo0U","name":"Saade","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p> </p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-bestiary/humanoids/half-elf/saade.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"person","relationships":[{"type":"person","id":"BINL89hHINUfeMxL","relationship":"Twin Brother","hidden":false}],"_lasttab":"details","role":"","location":"Rickety's Squibs","race":"Khorvar","gender":"Female","age":"92","pronoun":"She/Her","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"Sailor","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","fields":{"race":{"value":true},"gender":{"value":true},"age":{"value":true},"eyes":{"value":true},"skin":{"value":false},"hair":{"value":true},"pronoun":{"value":true},"profession":{"value":true},"voice":{"value":true},"faction":{"value":false},"height":{"value":true},"weight":{"value":true},"traits":{"value":true},"ideals":{"value":false},"bonds":{"value":false},"flaws":{"value":true},"longterm":{"value":true},"shortterm":{"value":true},"beliefs":{"value":true},"secret":{"value":true}},"scrollPos":"{\".tab.details .tab-inner\":0,\".tab.description .tab-inner\":0,\".relationships .items-list\":0}"},"_document-sheet-registrar":{"type":"person"},"journal-backlinks":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgiu42x0xnj","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar Lore#/CF_SEP/Lhazaar Principalities#/CF_SEP/02.09.12. People#/CF_SEP/Ship's Crew","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"mc3yxNeDEjdgPFMu","name":"Officer's Privy","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Officer's Privy</h1>\n<p>This small wash room has two privies and a wash basin.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L91WkUzg75E8tVjM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dljw0qnmnui","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Locations on the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"orwbw5L5w5FnQyv5","name":"Vala Doranetti","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>From Eston. Vala and Daina met in the House Deneith 85th on deployment. Vala came in as a replacement six months in, and her and Daina were soon inseparable. Vala had a bleak sense of humour that fed her optimism. She became a mercenary to escape some debts she owed to the wrong people in Eston. She was the only rank and file who Daina let her hair down around, and one time they were on leave in Seaside when Vala confided that she had joined House Deneith hoping that she would be sent to other countries before returning home.. She was fascinated by people and places that were overlooked, and was full of wanderlust and just wanted to see the world. She was the last person to see Daina before her desertion, she knew what Daina was planning and tried to get her to stay, but she swore she wouldn’t rat her out either. If Vala survived the Mourning, there’s a good chance she’s been looking for Daina — and doing so would give her a good excuse to indulge her wanderlust.</p>\n<p>Daina never looked for her because she is ashamed of having abandoned Vala, and the painful memories associated with that. But if Vala survived the Mourning, she would be looking for Daina, and keeping an ear out for rumours of her. Daina heard a rumour about a small group of Cyran veterans traveling the Principalities as some kind of Eberron A-Team, and that there was indeed an elven woman among them who fit Vala's description, but she's never encountered anyone who claims to be part of this group. </p>\n</div>","img":"modules/monks-enhanced-journal/assets/person.png","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"person","relationships":[{"type":"organization","id":"pnBZ8R4fkTBwT4Um","relationship":"Works for House Deneith","hidden":false}],"role":"","location":"Unknown","race":"Elf","gender":"Female","age":"","pronoun":"Her/She","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"Blademark","voice":"","faction":"House Deneith","height":"","weight":"","traits":"Vala is good with a spear, and comfortable with the more rough elements of society.  Someone you can count on when the chips are down.","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"She can be hot-headed.","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","_lasttab":"description","fields":{"race":{"value":true},"gender":{"value":true},"age":{"value":true},"eyes":{"value":true},"skin":{"value":false},"hair":{"value":true},"pronoun":{"value":true},"profession":{"value":true},"voice":{"value":true},"faction":{"value":true},"height":{"value":false},"weight":{"value":false},"traits":{"value":true},"ideals":{"value":false},"bonds":{"value":false},"flaws":{"value":true},"longterm":{"value":false},"shortterm":{"value":false},"beliefs":{"value":true},"secret":{"value":true}},"scrollPos":"{\".tab.details .tab-inner\":0,\".tab.description .tab-inner\":0,\".relationships .items-list\":0}"},"_document-sheet-registrar":{"type":"person"},"journal-backlinks":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_6nu2k3j5j03","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar Lore#/CF_SEP/Lhazaar Principalities#/CF_SEP/02.09.12. People#/CF_SEP/Potential Crew","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"pEqoQWGBvzZJZa4X","name":"Hersham the Unlucky","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Hersham is part of the Kolkarun family. Or at least, he was. It's not recommended to ask him about it. He is 30th in line to Kolkarun lordship, and he had a funny way of being placed in the wrong place at the wrong time during his early adulthood years. Hersham remains convinced his unluckiness is due to the machinations of some of his family members to keep him out of the way, although there always seemed to be a more convenient explanation for the clan to rely on. And so, he was in Aruldusk in Thrane when the war started, and joined up with the Brelish war efforts - there wasn't much else going on for him at the time. He eventually became fast friends with a younger dwarf mariner named Torlan, and the rest is history.</p>\n<p>They've served together on the Beggar's Bidding, where Hersham finally gained a bit of status as a gentleman and Torlan's first mate. Later, they wound up in the same prison camp in Cyre and were press-ganged onto the Fluttuante with Captain Alexei Aarland. When the prisoner exchange occurred, Hersham was unlucky... only Torlan went. But, I imagine he's kept up with his remarkable calligraphy practice since then.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-bestiary/humanoids/dwarf/morfius.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"person","relationships":[],"role":"","location":"Last Known is Regalport","race":"","gender":"","age":"","pronoun":"","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"","voice":"","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","scrollPos":"{\".tab.details .tab-inner\":0,\".tab.description .tab-inner\":0,\".relationships .items-list\":0}"},"_document-sheet-registrar":{"type":"person"},"journal-backlinks":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_6nu2k3j5j03","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar Lore#/CF_SEP/Lhazaar Principalities#/CF_SEP/02.09.12. People#/CF_SEP/Potential Crew","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"pNipelrrCIWs49wH","name":"Officers of the Storm Reaver","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Officers of the Storm Reaver</h1>\n<p>This is a complete listing of all the officers aboard the <em>Storm Reaver. </em>Aside from Mister Lagraa, Master Scourge, Krornik Kragshard, and Grok most of the the officers that serve aboard the Storm Reaver should not be influenced in the beginning of the adventure. They should play little role and the characters should see them on the periphery on the ship.</p>\n<h3>Prince Mika Rockface</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> captain, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile<br />Ruthless captain of the <em>Storm Reaver</em> and the ruler of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Cloudreaver Principality]{Cloudreaver Principality}.</p>\n<h3>Mister Lagraa</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female orc, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> first mate, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile<br />Rockface's bullying and sadistic first mate. She is second-in-command, and her rule is law on deck. She takes an immediate dislike to the PC's and any friends they make among the crew. She is terrified of the captain, however, and has more things on her mind than the PC's. She’s suspicious of everyone on the crew, and while he grows to hate the PCs, she does not sully his hands with fighting them unless they attack her, in which case she fights with relish, calling on her allies for aid in dealing with the “mutineers.” Boghi is a figure to be hated.</p>\n<h3>Master Scourge</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male half-orc, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> boatswain and master-at-arms, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile</p>\n<h3>Krornik \"Fishguts\" Kragshard</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> cook, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> neutral</p>\n<h3>\"Cut-Throat\" Grok</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female half-orc, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> quartermaster, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> neutral</p>\n<h3>Grovus Stormbeard</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> sorcerer, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> unfriendly<br />Sailing master, storm sorcerer, and old friend of the captains. Replaces Peppery Longfarthing. Grovus is part of Rockface's inner cirlce.</p>\n<h3>Riaris Krine</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male orc, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> master gunner, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> unfriendly<br />Part of Rockface's inner circle.</p>\n<h3>Hakrilli Quarne</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> articficer, carpenter, healer <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> unfriendly<br />Part of Rockface's inner circle.</p>\n<h3>Gragoth</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male orc, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> gunner's mate, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile<br />Bootlicker for Lagraa and Scourge.</p>\n<h3>Patch \"Salty\" Kolkrinun</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> boatswain's mate, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile<br />Sycophant of Lagraa and Scourge.</p>\n<h3>\"Caulky\" Tarroon</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female halfling, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> cabin girl, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> uncooperative</p>\n<h3>Owlbear Hartshorn</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male orc, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> none, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> neutral<br />Simplton and \"pet\" of Mr. Lagraa.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":13},"cf":{"id":"temp_rxb9n4yk7i","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Crew of the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"q3nwua0RWiLVWbSI","name":"Draci's Wondrous Alchemical Exchange","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2>Location</h2>\n<p>Half way up the western cliff face off a wooden pathway, built into the cliffside at the very edge of the cave. The street outside is strewn with debris from an overturned cart and a ragged male halfling with a missing arm is raving about how the Last War has not ended.</p>\n<h2>Description</h2>\n<p>The shop is a slate grey stone structure built into the cave opening in the cliff. There are carved wooden doors and the wall stretching facing the outside cliffface has numerous overgrown but well tended planter boxes.</p>\n<p>The decor inside is antique style from many generations ago. The shopkeeper has a display of exotic coins and trinkets on display behind the main counter.</p>\n<h2>Shopkeeper</h2>\n<p>Owned by a male dwarf, with a long braided beard decorated with rings of precious metals. His name is Draci, he seems to know the name of everyone that enters his shop.</p>\n<p> </p>\n</div>","img":"modules/monks-enhanced-journal/assets/shop.png","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"shop","purchasing":"locked","items":[{"_id":"ZCKshQqdLA5rFMLZ","name":"Potion of Lion's Roar","type":"gear","img":"icons/consumables/potions/bottle-bulb-corked-labeled-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Bottle of thick yellowish-brown liquid with a lion's nail in it.</p>\n<p>The potion duplicates the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait}</em> power limited to the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation] skill.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait}</em>; 25 gp</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0.25,"price":"50 gp","equippable":true,"equipped":false,"isArcaneDev