{"_id":"uSYbNNrWZ5wEJo7r","name":"The Money Pit","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">The Money Pit</h1>\n<p>Owen McDougal is the town drunk and known locally for his tall tales of buried treasure. None of the locals take him seriously, but he earns a few pieces of eight keeping them entertained on stormy nights. While the group is in town a storm strikes, forcing the characters to take shelter in one of the larger shacks. Owen is present in the small crowd of locals sheltering in the same accommodation. As the storm reaches its height Owen begins his tale.</p>\n<aside class=\"read-aloud\">\n<p>“Arrr, ’twas four years ago this very day I came across the strange pit in the woods east of here. Perhaps I wouldn’t have even noticed it, all covered in fallen branches as it were, if I hadn’t been drinking and stumbled inta the hole. As I lay on me back I gazed up and there, swaying in the trees was an old block and tackle.</p>\n<p>“Naturally, I thought to meself I’d found some buried treasure. I got meself a pick and shovel and went back the next day to begin digging. Two feet down I hit stone. These weren’t no ordinary stones but flagstones, all square and proper like. Beneath was a filled-in shaft with signs of pick marks on the edge—surely the work of pirates burying their loot!</p>\n<p>“I kept on digging ‘til at ten feet I hit wood. Sadly ’twas no chest but a layer of planks laid across the pit. Sensing gold lay just beneath I carried on but after 25 feet I was beaten. ’T’would need a crew of men to carry on digging.</p>\n<p>“You all remember how I came back all excited and like don’t yer? And none of you would take me seriously! Well, I tried digging further meself but ’twas no use. It wasn’t a job for one man so I filled in the hole and gave up. It’s still there now, all that treasure, just waiting to be dug up.”</p>\n</aside>\n<p>McDougal’s tale is well-known to the locals. Many of them have seen the site of his excavation but there is no proof buried treasure exists and the locals lack the skill and equipment—as well as the inclination—to follow up the matter.</p>\n<p>Excavating the pit from the surface is no easy task. It extends for 80 feet with planks of wood sealed with clay and coconut fiber every ten to fifteen feet beneath the 25 feet mark. Worse still, breaching a wooden layer at 60 feet causes the pit to flood. No matter how fast the group bails the water keeps refilling. There is no way to prevent the shaft flooding—even magic fails to stem the flow. A clue to how to reach the treasure lies in the water, however—it is seawater.</p>\n<p>The bottom of the shaft is located in the ceiling of one of the numerous sea caverns located beneath the island. This particular cavern is lower than those around it and has numerous water channels feeding it from above and the sides. In effect, the bottom of the shaft is below sea level.</p>\n<p>Locating the correct cavern requires the characters to swim in the bloodfish-infested caverns. Every character may make a Smarts (–4) roll for each 30 minutes spent searching. The character scoring the highest success spots the shaft extending upward from the cavern roof. Each roll, successful or not, brings the characters into contact with one or more swarms of bloodfish.</p>\n<p>The treasure is located on a series of tarred wooden planks 10 feet up the shaft. Note thatSavage Tales 157 the planks, while protected from rot, are not joined together—water can get through with ease. Reaching it requires the character to break one or more planks, causing the treasure to fall into the cavern.</p>\n<p>Salvaging the treasure in this method takes four hours less one hour per success and raise on a Swimming roll (to a minimum of one hour). Again, each roll requires the characters to deal with hungry bloodfish.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_4s6bxi84dvu","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Savage Tales#/CF_SEP/The Dragonshards","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"v4w8i8JJjzYB75fO","name":"Workshop","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Workshop</h1>\n<p>This cramped room is shared by @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Grovus Stormbread]{Grovus Stormbread} and @Compendium[savage-tales-pirates-of-cyre.pirates-of-cyre-bestiary.Hakrilli Quarne]{Hakrilli Quarne}. This room is obviously an arcane workshop chalk full of over stuffed book shelves, a couple work benches, and a table in the center of the room. Ever available space is filled with equipment, tools, and unfinished experiments. There are numerous curiosities and unsettling objects in here that either <span style=\"color:#3598db\">Grovus </span>or <span style=\"color:#3598db\">Hakrilli </span>are studying.</p>\n<p>There are any numerous potions, scrolls, and minor magical items that can be found here. With the disorder that is present here it is more likely to steal something here that will go unnoticed. If one can get past the good lock on the door and the trapped handle.</p>\n<h2 class=\"trap\">Shocking Trap</h2>\n<p><strong>Type:</strong> Magical; <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} Check:</strong> Yes, at –2; <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} Check:</strong> Yes, at –3</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger:</strong> If someone who tries to open the door does not speak <span style=\"color:#e67e23\">\"Devourer protect us\"</span>, will active the trap.</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> The door handle triggers an electrical shock dealing ([[/r 2d6x=]] damage).</p>\n<p> </p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L91WkUzg75E8tVjM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dljw0qnmnui","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Locations on the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"vmlCjdWCyrYJxvxn","name":"Crew of the Storm Reaver","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h1 class=\"wide\">Crew of the Storm Reaver</h1>\n<h2>Swabs</h2>\n<h3>Sandara Quinn</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female human, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> swab, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> helpful<br />Cleric of Arawai, only firm ally the party will have from the start.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}</p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:1.125em\">Giffer Tibbs</span></h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> swab, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> neutral<br />A bedraggled dwarf with one eye.</p>\n<h3>Rosie Cusswell</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> swab, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> neutral<br />Short even for a dwarf, Rosie Cusswell is fierce and has more muscles than most of the crew. She also has a fouler mouth than all the crew put together. Rosie is from Cliffscrape, and like the characters was impressed onto the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> crew. She has been on the ship for over a week and has already made her mark threatening others who mess with her. She has a healthy hatred of Mr. Dabrak and Scourge. She loves food, drink, and tall tales. Anyone who provides her with any of those gains a +1 bonus to any check to influence her. She is missing her fiddle, and has been unable to convince Grok to give it back to her. Any character that can recover her fiddle for her, will immediately made a firm friend of Rosie.</p>\n<h3>Tamroth Scrimshaw</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female orc, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> swab, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> neutral<br />Young lass that is talented in carving scrimshaw.</p>\n<h3>\"Badger\" Stonehurler</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> swab, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> uncooperative<br />An old dwarf who has his gray hear shaved into strips.</p>\n<h3>Tilly Tordanthan</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> swab, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> uncooperative<br />A tough joker that likes her rum.</p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:1.125em\">Aretta Tarravan</span></h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female half-orc, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> swab, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> unfriendly<br />A bad tempered harlot whose only signs of orc heritage are big orc ears and on larger incisor.</p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:1.125em\">Arzag</span></h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male hobgoblin, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> swab, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> unfriendly<br />A very tall hobgolbin ex-slaver with a bald head.</p>\n<h3>Crimson \"Cog\" Cogward</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male human, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> swab, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> unfriendly<br />Crimson Cogward (so called after the color his neck turns when he’s angry) is a loner, and prone to incredible rages and dark moods. Cog gets pleasure from little other than combat and is quick to get into fistfights, whether because of a chance remark or simple bad luck. Cog actually volunteered to join the crew of the <em>Storm Reaver</em>. He has spent his first few days aboard stealing and secreting away goods for barter. Cog loves dark tales. A character that can succeed on telling a dark tale to Cog will gain a +1 bonus on checks to influence Cog. Characters who are fighters and favor muscle over talk, interspursing their talk with grisly details will gain a +1 bonus to influence Cog. However, a failed check is likely to elicit a violent response from the angry sailor.</p>\n<h3>Sador Chumlett</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male orc, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> swab, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> unfriendly<br />A fat, pushy bully with a shaved head.</p>\n<h3>Jaundiced Sudak</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> swab, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile<br />A humorless, greedy mute.</p>\n<h3>Jakes Magpie</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> swab, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile<br />A thief caught stealing from the quartermaster's store and sentenced to keelhauling on the character's first day.</p>\n<h2>Riggers</h2>\n<h3>Barefoot Shamms</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> rigger, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> neutral<br />A former fisherwoman from Port Krez who never wears shoes.</p>\n<h3>Conchobhar Turlach Tomraan</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male gnome, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> rigger, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> uncooperative<br />Conchobhar Tomraan is a handsome, honey-tongued gnome who wears a foppish purple hat, an eye patch, and a white silk shirt, and carries a dandyish cane. His appearance is that of someone pretending to be a pirate, rather than a true buccaneer. Conchobhar is a professional gambler who made the mistake of drinking with the <em>Storm Reaver’s</em> crew one night. He has been on ship less than 24 hours at the start of the adventure. Conchobhar is resigned to his fate but is determined to make the most of it, as he’s always yearned for the sea anyway. One thing dominates Conchobhar’s thinking—himself. Conchobhar is also a serial womanizer, and female characters gain a +1 bonus on all checks to influence him. He finds Rosie Cusswell magnificent.</p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:1.125em\">\"Ratline\" Rattsberger</span></h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> rigger, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> uncooperative<br />A rat-faced dwarf with slightly longer arms and three missing fingers.</p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:1.125em\">Maheem</span></h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male human, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> rigger, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile<br />A big man with a permanent scowl.</p>\n<h3>Slippery Syl</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> rigger, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile<br />An unhinged murderer who fled to sea to escape the gallows.</p>\n<h3>Tam \"Narwhal\" Tate</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> rigger, <span style=\"color:#ba372a\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile<br />An old friend of Master Scourge with a large ugly nose and half an ear.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":4},"cf":{"id":"temp_rxb9n4yk7i","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Crew of the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
