{"_id":"zl3AxvpKGpApJn3z","name":"Cut-Throat Grok","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Cut-Throat Grok (N female half-orc fighter 5) is the <em>Storm Reaver's</em> quartermaster, a no-nonsense character with a huge scar across her neck. Growing up among pirates is tough for anyone unusual, and Grok got her scar fighting a gang of cutthroats in the alleys of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Port Verge]{Port Verge} who robbed her and left her for dead when she was only 11 years old. Grok is a reedy half-orc who favors dark clothing. She carries a notched greataxe and an array of throwing axes hangs from her belt. Grok frequently grins toothily, and uses appalling curse words, particularly when drunk. Grok is renowned for being tough, and she doesn’t suffer fools, but she is a close friend of Ambrose Kroop, whom she sees as someone who’s had even worse luck than she’s had.</p>\n<p>Grok is usually found in the quartermaster’s store (area A9) during the day. In the evenings, she locks the store and carouses on deck, drinking and gambling with the other pirates before returning to her cabin (area A7) to sleep it off.</p>\n<p>Grok loves unusual drink and fine songs, and a character who provides her with at least 20 gp worth of alcohol that isn’t rum or who makes a successful DC 15 Perform (song) check gains a +4 bonus on all checks made to influence her. If Grok is made friendly, she allows the PCs into the quartermaster’s store after normal hours, where PCs can negotiate for equipment with her with additional Diplomacy checks. Recovering a PC’s starting equipment is considered simple aid (DC +0), a loan of goods worth up to 150 gp is considered lengthy aid (DC +5), and a loan of 300 gp worth of equipment is considered dangerous aid that could result in punishment, since she might get keelhauled herself for theft (DC +15).</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/icons/pirates-of-cyre.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":4,"type":"base","role":"Quartermaster","location":"The Wormwood","race":"Female Half-Orc","gender":"","age":"","eyes":"","skin":"","hair":"","profession":"","voice":"Gravelly","faction":"","height":"","weight":"","traits":"","ideals":"","bonds":"","flaws":"","longterm":"","shortterm":"","beliefs":"","secret":"","DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":{"notes":""},"scrollPos":"{\".description\":0}"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_rxb9n4yk7i","path":"Mourners of Lhazaar#/CF_SEP/Season 1: Mutiny Against the Cloudreavers#/CF_SEP/The Storm Reaver#/CF_SEP/Crew of the Storm Reaver","color":"#000000"},"_document-sheet-registrar":{"type":"base"}}}
{"_id":"zo1EzNO2guxNKxWk","name":"The Lazy Board","content":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<h2>Location</h2>\n<p>On Cliff's Edge in the lower ward near a rune carved stone, next to a brothel named the <em>Loose Nymph</em> and a lift up from the docks.</p>\n<h2>Decsription</h2>\n<p>The inn is a small half-timbered building, with a single salvaged stone wall and roughly hewn wooden tables and benches. Numerous boards hang from the walls that do not seem to support anything nor be fully connected.</p>\n<h2>Innkeeper</h2>\n<p>An old curmudgeon dwarf named The Baron. No one knows what is real name is. There is no dog on the premises, but there are eight different cats. He was once an adventurer and pirate, but retired after his companions and ship where attacked by a tribe of Saughin. Only he surived as a warning to those that don't pay the fees of the Sea Devils.</p>\n<h2>Notice Board Listings</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Someone stole my chicken that lays all sort of metal eggs. Help me find it.</li>\n<li>TEST SUBJECT NEEDED! We at the Barrington Bakery (insert your own name) are looking for subjects to test out our new magical breads. We infuse magic into the mixing process for a, hopefully, tasteful bread. You will need to taste each bread, and have our scholar review the side effects. You will be paid per day.</li>\n<li>Help wanted t' return me property: Yesterday some o' th' young neighborhood scalawags stole me carved wooden leg while I were pissed in th' gutter outside th' Salty Strumpet. I can nah chase aft them t' git it back 'cause me backup leg be mor'n ghastly. If'n ye can get back me leg I'll pay ye 10 gold, it holds a lot o' sentimental-type meanin' t' me.</li>\n<li>100 List: Help! Local bard needs assistance creating a list of 100 dirty jobs no one wants to do. A small payment will be available as well as your name as a contributing author in the book I'm writing.</li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"secret gm-secret\">\n<h2>Rumors</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Tally May house is north of the town. Yeah she's collect cats. Lots of cats. The place smells like urine and half the cats are dead. Someone once told me that those dead cats can move.</li>\n<li>There was an accident at the fighters guild which resulted in the death of a member but it has been hushed up and those responsible will never be held to account</li>\n<li>The tavernkeep at the Lusty Robster is actually a famous war hero trying to keep a low profile.</li>\n<li>The old hermit came into town the other day. He said the old dam up river is leaking. No one believes him, because he's crazy. That dam hasn't broke in hundreds of years.</li>\n<li>Brose has been spending strange coins, each bearing the image of a fanged skull</li>\n<li>A lost child was found with a spell book. The authorities are investigating.</li>\n<li>Ghosts walk the ramparts of Modison's Hold during the full moon</li>\n<li>Krieg was heard arguing with a stranger the other night, now he has disappeared.</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>","img":"modules/monks-enhanced-journal/assets/shop.png","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{"type":"shop","purchasing":"locked","items":[{"_id":"4jpUk6dk1sajQRIZ","name":"Grog (mug)","type":"gear","img":"icons/consumables/drinks/alcohol-beer-stein-wooden-metal-brown.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":"2 cp","equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isArcaneDevice":false,"arcaneSkillDie":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"powerPoints":{"value":null,"max":null},"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":4,"cost":"3 cp"},"effects":[],"folder":"SDyok7IqZQpyflF3","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration